    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.35c.8"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">8</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">NEBRASKA LIBRARY ASSOCIATION</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>October 21, 1971</dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Dr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>Lincoln, Nebraska, and Columbia, Missouri</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Since the wording of the plaque we have presented to you as a symbol of the Mari Sandoz Award is necessarily limited, the Nebraska Library Association members would like to add our expression of deep satisfaction with your being the first recipient.</p>
                
                <p>The guidelines for the Mari Sandoz Award state that "the nominee shall have made specific and significant contributions to the book world of Nebraska thorugh the printed word, film production, or other realted activities." Your magnificent epic, <hi rend="underline">A Cycle of the West</hi>, would in itself, place you at the top of the list of nominees. With the filming of <hi rend="caps">Black Elk Speaks</hi>, with your other writings, your teaching, and your television appearances, you are contributing in every way we could possibly imagine to the "book world of Nebraska."</p>
                
                <p>The other guideline for choice of nominee is that "he shall have 'ties' to Nebraska." Who could have greater "ties" than our Poet Laureate of fifty years?</p> 
                
                <p>This Award is to be presented only at the discretion of the Nebraska Library Association Executive Board. The Association has been given the opportunity ot maintain high standards by your acceptance of the first Mari Sandoz Award.</p> 
                <closer>
                    <salute>With sincere appreciation,</salute> 
                    
                    <hi rend="caps">NEBRASKA LIBRARY ASSOCIATION</hi> 
                    <signed>Kathlyn K. Lundgren</signed> 
                    <signed>Kathlyn K. Lundgren, President</signed>
                    <signed>Jeanne Bogard</signed>
                    <signed>Jeanne Bogard, Chairman, Citations Committee</signed> 
                </closer>
                
                <fw>2</fw>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
